    <section class="tokyo">
      <h2> Explore Munich </h2>
      <ul>
        <li><h3>Popular Sites</h3></li>
          <li><h4> Marienplatz</h4></li>
          <p> Marienplatz is the city center of Munich. Here you can access
          Munich's metro system, find many great beer halls and restaurants, and
        view Munich's historic architecture </p>
          <li><h4> Frauenkirche  </h4><li>
          <p> This very massive church located by Marienplatz was bombed during
          World War 2, but restored after the war. The two towers give a great view
        of the entire city, and Munich's historic buildings. </p>
            <p></p>
        <li><h3>Entertainment</h3></li>
          <li><h4> BMW Musuem</h4></li>
          <p> The BMW Musuem is located just outside Munich's city limits, right
          next to the 1972 Olympic park. Here, you can learn about the history
        of Germany's most well known vehicle from the first engine, to World War II, to
        its high performance cars that are known today.</p>

          <li><h4> 089 </h4></li>
          <p> 089 is a well known bar/club that is popular with the younger crowd.
          clubs in Munich are 18 and up, so it's very popular amongst college aged
        individuals. </p>
            <p></p>
        <li><h3>Restaraunts</h3></li>
        <li><h4> Holfbrauhaus</h4></li>
        <p> This famous beer hall is known to have great beer and great food. Enjoy
        a full Liter of beer with complimentary pretzels on the side </p>
        <li><h4> Augustiner-Brau Munchen </h4></li>
        <p> Yes, another beer hall but that is what Munich is known for. This beer hall
        offers a variety of different brews with great food. </p>
          <p></p>
        <li><h3>Transportation</h3></li>
        <li><h4> Metro Train</h4></li>
        <p> The fastest and easiest way around Munich is by Metro train. The metro
        runs underneith the city and serves many stations in Munich as well as the
      surrounding area.</p>

      </ul>
    </section>
  </aside>
